article.headline: S. Utah 56, IUPUI 53
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Swaney Cooper scored 12 points and grabbed seven rebounds to lead Southern Utah to a 56-53 win over IUPUI on Saturday. Justin Allen had nine points and Nurudeen Adepoju added eight points and four rebounds for the Thunderbirds (12-8, 2-3 Mid-Continent Conference). Billy Pettiford led IUPUI with 10 points and eight rebounds. David Barlow added nine points for the Jaguars (8-10, 2-3) in their second home loss of the season. Austin Montgomery hit a jumper with 4:18 remaining to cap an 8-0 IUPUI run and cut the Southern Utah lead to one point, but the Jaguars scored only one basket the rest of the game. Cooper blocked a potential game-tying 3-pointer by Barlow with two seconds to play.
